"<b>Faki soupa</b>" (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../887/11887.xml">
Greek</link>:φακή,φακές)is a Greek type of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../298/19651298.xml">
soup</link> based on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../455/174455.xml">
lentil</link>s. The preparation of the dish is quite simple, but the result is a very healthy and filling meal. Usual ingredients are <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../258/51258.xml">
onions</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../739/5985739.xml">
carrot</link>s, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../206/23206.xml">
parsley</link> and sometimes <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../234/9940234.xml">
tomato</link> sauce or <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../762/32762.xml">
vinegar</link>. Greek families may just have a single plate of "fakes" -as the dish is simply called- usually for lunch, without accompanying it with side dishes or salads. However, it goes perfectly with white cheeses such as <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../892/277892.xml">
feta</link> or brown <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../969/36969.xml">
bread</link> such as "mavro".
